    verse:'Love is patient, love is kind. It does not envy, it does not boast, it is not proud.',
    ref:'1 Corinthians 13:4',
    imgQuery:'Masasa Beach clear water Batangas Philippines',
    story:'Paul wrote a beautiful letter to the church in Corinth, and inside it is one of the most famous descriptions of love ever written. He wanted people to understand what real, godly love actually looks like in action.\n\nHe said love is patient — it waits without getting angry. Love is kind — it looks for ways to help, not hurt. Love doesn\'t envy what others have, doesn\'t brag about itself, and isn\'t puffed up with pride.\n\nThis kind of love isn\'t just a warm feeling. It\'s a daily choice — choosing patience when someone is slow, choosing kindness when someone is grumpy, choosing to celebrate a friend\'s success instead of feeling jealous.\n\nGod loves us exactly this way — patiently, kindly, without keeping score. And He invites us to love others the very same way, one small choice at a time.',
